DURBAN - The KwaZulu-Natal Basic Education Department is on the brink of collapse. Teachers union Natu is levelling a number of allegations of corruption against officials at the department. It says there’s something dodgy about the overproduction of sanitary towels. According to the union, the department had budgeted R20-million but has so far spent over R100-million. It says the sanitary towels produced don’t meet industry standards. The union says the national Department of Basic Education has agreed to investigate all the allegations its flagged. KwaZulu-Natal officials said they need more time to look into the claims before responding. * Watch the full video report by Thuba Vilane in the gallery above. eNCA